Star Wars Insider 145 (2013)


English | CBR | 84 pages | 64.98 MB


Genres: Science-Fiction
Series: Star Wars Insider (Newsstand Edition)
Publisher: Titan


Star Wars Insider 145 is the 123rd issue of the magazine Star Wars Insider and the 53rd published by Titan Magazines. In Star Wars Insider, we'll be solving the riddle of Darth Vader. Is he the Star Wars saga's most dastardly villain, or its greatest hero? We'll be asking the experts. You'll never look at him the same way again! Plus, we'll have the latest details about the hotly anticipated new animated series, Star Wars: Rebels! There will also be an update on Episode VII as principal production nears. Plus, you can win a signed copy of the all-new Making of Return of the Jedi book and we'll tell you how to make your votes count in the Star Wars Insider awards! Available in Newsstand and PREVIEWS Exclusive Cover Editions!


Issue highlights:

Topps' exclusive!
Is the Sith Lord a victim or villain?!
An exclusive discussion about the first Star Wars' sequel novel!
We have a discussion with the artists McCaig & Chiang!
Author L. Neil Smith on the classic trilogy of Lando novels!!
Brand-new tale featuring Princess Leia!
